blog.description: hey what up, my name's kait, i'm 19 and I never learned how to stop crying about taylor swift. reputation tour glendale, az.

summary:
To absolutely get sappy on main, I wanted to make a post about the nearing end of this era.
The Reputation era was the first...
body:
To absolutely get sappy on main, I wanted to make a post about the nearing end of this era.

The Reputation era was the first time that I had ever actually been a part of the fandom, despite being a fan of Taylor for 10+ years, and it’s been kind of amazing. I’ve gotten to see all the way from everyone freaking out about cryptic snake videos, to the Secret Sessions, to the opening night of tour, to the 123lgb meme, to the surprise songs every night, to the end of tour and, finally, the tour movie.

I didn’t get super close with a lot of people, but to those that I spoke to; to those who reached out a hand or even dropped a kind word passing by, i wanna thank you. I wanna thank the girl who i met at the concert, who’s name I didn’t catch, but who complimented my shirt, who talked to me about Taylor’s hints about the tour on her Instagram, and who took a picture for my mom and I. These small acts of kindness mean the world to me. Thank you.

And I wanna thank you @taylorswift as always for opening up your heart and your life to the world. This era has been an amazing experience, and I can’t wait until the next one comes ‘round. You and your music have enriched my life and helped me to grow from the pain I’ve endured, and I hope to someday give you a hug that shows you just how much I mean that.

Anyway, stream the reputation tour movie on new years eve🤪
